	<h3>Activation Request Parameters (1)</h3>

	A <strong>page render request</strong> can also include query parameters in <strong>key=value</strong> fashion, 
	which Tapestry calls <strong>activation request parameters</strong>.<br/><br/>
	
	To specify activation request parameters in a PageLink, use the <code>parameters</code> parameter. 
	Here we have specified <code>parameters="queryParams"</code>.
	
  	<div class="eg">
		<t:pagelink page="examples/navigation/ActivationRequestParameters2" parameters="queryParams">Show Person ${personId}</t:pagelink><br/>
	</div>
	
	The link has a URL similar to this: <code>http://thehost/jumpstart/examples/navigation/activationrequestparameters2?personid=1</code> 
	See the activation request parameters appended to the end?<br/><br/>
	
	Click the link above to learn more.<br/><br/>
	
